DEVELOP SETTINGS:


-------------------------- ENV --------------------------------

create in root dir dev.env file for dev mode. Fill in the following gaps:
ENV=LOCAL
HOST=127.0.0.1
PORT=8888


create in root dir prod.env file for prod mode, if you need it. Fill in the following gaps:
ENV=*Use your settings

HOST=*Use your settings
PORT=*Use your settings


run python app: python3 main.py

fake test request on localhost: 
echo '<134>Sep 15 18:25:43 my-nginx-host nginx: 31.28.159.255 client42 admin [15/Sep/2025:18:25:43 +0200] "GET /index.html HTTP/1.1" 200 1024 "-" "Mozilla/5.0"' | nc 127.0.0.1 8888

